fg_segments: EPAM Systems, Inc., together with its subsidiaries ("EPAM") has created this Privacy Policy in line with our commitment to your privacy on EPAM websites.
The following discloses our information gathering, dissemination and protection practices.
By accessing this site you agree to the terms of the EPAM Privacy Policy outlined below.
If you do not agree to the terms of this policy, please do not access or use this site.
EPAM collects information to provide better services to our users. We collect information in two ways:

information you affirmatively choose to submit to us (such as your name, e-mail address, company name, title, country) for the purpose of accessing various downloads, viewing specific content, subscribing to EPAM newsletters, etc.; information we get from your use of our websites, such as the IP address, browser type, ISP, referring/exit pages, platform type, date/time stamp, number of clicks, domain name and country/state of all visitors to the site; and location information: when you use EPAM's websites, we may collect and process information about your actual location. We use various technologies and tools to determine location.

Cookies This Cookie Policy applies to any websites, branded pages on third party platforms (such as Facebook or LinkedIn), and applications accessed or used through such websites or third party platforms ("EPAM Sites") which are operated by or on behalf of EPAM Systems.
We use a number of suppliers that may also set cookies on your device on our behalf when you visit the EPAM Sites to allow them to deliver the services they are providing.
More information about these cookies may be available on the relevant third party's website.
If you do not agree to our use of cookies in this way, you should set your browser settings accordingly or not use EPAM Sites.
If you disable the cookies that we use, this may affect your user experience while on EPAM Sites. Use of information

Any information collected by EPAM will be done in accordance with this privacy policy for the purposes of making better business decisions, supporting the activities you choose to engage in, and providing higher quality solutions and services to our customers.
We use your location information to tailor your EPAM website experience.
We also may use any non-personal information we collect to enhance our web site, and your IP address for web site diagnostics and administration.
We will not sell, share, or rent this information, for commercial purposes, to any person or organization.
EPAM process information we collect on our servers in many countries around the world.
We may process your information on a server located outside the country where you live.

EPAM treats your personal information as Confidential Information. We protect this confidential Information by storing it on secure servers that only select EPAM personnel have access to, and by encrypting it to help prevent access by any unauthorized parties.
This website contains links to various third party web sites.
EPAM has no control over, and is not responsible for the content, privacy policies or reliability of such sites.
EPAM reserves the right to modify or amend this Privacy Policy at its own discretion.
The changes can be viewed here or elsewhere at this site.
Your continued usage of this site will mean you accept those changes.

raw_html:
EPAM Systems, Inc., together with its subsidiaries (“EPAM”) has created this Privacy Policy in line with our commitment to your privacy on EPAM websites. The following discloses our information gathering, dissemination and protection practices.

Compliance

By accessing this site you agree to the terms of the EPAM Privacy Policy outlined below. If you do not agree to the terms of this policy, please do not access or use this site.

Collection of information

EPAM collects information to provide better services to our users. We collect information in two ways:

information you affirmatively choose to submit to us (such as your name, e-mail address, company name, title, country) for the purpose of accessing various downloads, viewing specific content, subscribing to EPAM newsletters, etc.;
information we get from your use of our websites, such as the IP address, browser type, ISP, referring/exit pages, platform type, date/time stamp, number of clicks, domain name and country/state of all visitors to the site; and
location information: when you use EPAM’s websites, we may collect and process information about your actual location. We use various technologies and tools to determine location.


Cookies
This Cookie Policy applies to any websites, branded pages on third party platforms (such as Facebook or LinkedIn), and applications accessed or used through such websites or third party platforms (“EPAM Sites”) which are operated by or on behalf of EPAM Systems.
We use a number of suppliers that may also set cookies on your device on our behalf when you visit the EPAM Sites to allow them to deliver the services they are providing. More information about these cookies may be available on the relevant third party's website.
If you do not agree to our use of cookies in this way, you should set your browser settings accordingly or not use EPAM Sites. If you disable the cookies that we use, this may affect your user experience while on EPAM Sites.
Use of information

Any information collected by EPAM will be done in accordance with this privacy policy for the purposes of making better business decisions, supporting the activities you choose to engage in, and providing higher quality solutions and services to our customers. We use your location information to tailor your EPAM website experience. We also may use any non-personal information we collect to enhance our web site, and your IP address for web site diagnostics and administration. We will not sell, share, or rent this information, for commercial purposes, to any person or organization. EPAM process information we collect on our servers in many countries around the world. We may process your information on a server located outside the country where you live.

Information security

EPAM treats your personal information as Confidential Information. We protect this confidential Information by storing it on secure servers that only select EPAM personnel have access to, and by encrypting it to help prevent access by any unauthorized parties.

Links

This website contains links to various third party web sites. EPAM has no control over, and is not responsible for the content, privacy policies or reliability of such sites.

Changes to the Policy

EPAM reserves the right to modify or amend this Privacy Policy at its own discretion. The changes can be viewed here or elsewhere at this site. Your continued usage of this site will mean you accept those changes.
